programme.title: Secret Lives of the Super Rich (New York's Finest Address & The $3 Million Hybrid Ferrari) S1 (n°604)
programme.desc: «New York's Finest Address & The $3 Million Hybrid Ferrari»Step inside one of the most prestigious residences ever to hit the market in NYC, high atop the iconic Plaza Hotel. Buckle up in an uber-rare hybrid sports car worth millions. Try these on for size: the most expensive diamond earrings ever sold at auction. Toast with a $2,500 cocktail in a sin city watering hole owned by a music megastar. Tour a Beverly Hills modern mansion packed with millions in art and custom furniture. Get a look inside iconic rides that are miniature models of the real deal, and at five figures each, are the ultimate "super models". Get VIP access to an ultra-exclusive show jumping competition, where the horses are worth millions and their riders are worth billions. Check out the most expensive American car ever sold at auction, the very first Shelby Cobra ever made.

programme.title: Open du Texas
programme.desc: Valero Texas Open is a professional golf tournament on the PGA Tour, played near San Antonio, Texas. It is the sixth oldest professional golf tournament worldwide, the third oldest on the PGA Tour and the longest held in the same city, and many renowned players have won it, including Sam Snead, Ben Hogan, and Arnold Palmer.

programme.title: Rallye : Abu Dhabi Desert Challenge
programme.desc: The Abu Dhabi Desert Challenge is one of the world's most prestigious international cross country rallies held in the Emirate of Abu Dhabi of the United Arab Emirates since 1991. Over the years the rally has seen some biggest names in international motorsport in the dunes of the UAE, including Carlos Sainz, Colin McRae, Ari Vatenan, and Heinz Kinigadner. Originally the challenge was for cars only, and motorcycles and quads are allowed since 1995 and trucks since 2002.
